        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 PW/1–1846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-18T17:00:00+03:00">January 18, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 18—1:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. ReDeptel 36, January 8. Note dated January 18 from Foreign Office states:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Soviet Govt has appointed to International Military Tribunal, in Tokyo
                            for the trial of the chief <gloss target="#t_Jap1">Jap</gloss> war
                            criminals Director of Juridical <pb facs="0403" n="391" xml:id="pg_391"/> Sciences, Minister S. A. Golunsky as [associate] prosecutor for the
                            Soviet Union and Major General of Justice I. M. Zaryanov as a judicial
                            member of the military collegium of the supreme court of the USSR.<note n="99" xml:id="d302fn1">Apparently garbled; Zaryanov was nominated
                                as judge for the Tribunal.</note> They will depart with their staff
                            from Moscow for Tokyo in next few days.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
